36#include "krb5_locl.h"
37
38static krb5_error_code
39ARCFOUR_string_to_key(krb5_context context,
40 krb5_enctype enctype,
41 krb5_data password,
42 krb5_salt salt,
43 krb5_data opaque,
44 krb5_keyblock *key)
45{
46 krb5_error_code ret;
47 uint16_t *s = NULL;
48 size_t len = 0, i;
49 EVP_MD_CTX *m;
50
51 m = EVP_MD_CTX_create();
52 if (m == NULL) {
53 ret = krb5_enomem(context);
54 goto out;
55 }
56
57 EVP_DigestInit_ex(m, EVP_md4(), NULL);
58
59 ret = wind_utf8ucs2_length(password.data, &len);
60 if (ret) {
61 krb5_set_error_message (context, ret,
62 N_("Password is not valid UTF-8", ""));
63 goto out;
64 }
65
66 s = malloc (len * sizeof(s[0]));
67 if (len != 0 && s == NULL) {
68 ret = krb5_enomem(context);
69 goto out;
70 }
71
72 ret = wind_utf8ucs2(password.data, s, &len);
73 if (ret) {
74 krb5_set_error_message (context, ret,
75 N_("Password is not valid UTF-8", ""));
76 goto out;
77 }
78
79 /* LE encoding */
80 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
81 unsigned char p;
82 p = (s[i] & 0xff);
83 EVP_DigestUpdate (m, &p, 1);
84 p = (s[i] >> 8) & 0xff;
85 EVP_DigestUpdate (m, &p, 1);
86 }
87
88 key->keytype = enctype;
89 ret = krb5_data_alloc (&key->keyvalue, 16);
90 if (ret) {
91 krb5_enomem(context);
92 goto out;
93 }
94 EVP_DigestFinal_ex (m, key->keyvalue.data, NULL);
95
96 out:
97 EVP_MD_CTX_destroy(m);
98 if (s)
99 memset (s, 0, len);
100 free (s);
101 return ret;
102}
103
104struct salt_type _krb5_arcfour_salt[] = {
105 {
106 KRB5_PW_SALT,
107 "pw-salt",
108 ARCFOUR_string_to_key
109 },
110 { 0, NULL, NULL }
111};
